Psychology of Overlays: Why do we spend more money?
The auction participants are likely to spend more money and overvalue the product.
Neurologists and economists at the University of New York discovered the neurological - economic bases of this known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to the study in Science magazine, people do not want to lose in competitions such as eBay auctions, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
Scientists tried to establish the neurological scheme of this "game" through experimental auctions.
One of the volunteer groups played lottery, the other took part in a auction and while the functional magnetic resonance system (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could earn money, but during auctions, where it is fundamental to bet more than the other, losing the game intensified the operation of the complex called strata located below the cerebral cortex.
This area of the brain, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of self-priming nervous system.
According to scientists, the increase in bets is explained as a prevention in order not to cause an intense reaction of the stratum.
To support their theory, the economists of the scientific group also conducted a financial follow-up study.
In this experiment three groups wagered against one person under different circumstances.
The control group was simply informed of the actual value of the product in question, and its members were betting.
In addition, another group was promised that if they won, they would receive $15 more prizes.
On the other hand, the third group received exactly $15 before the auction, but in case of losing the auction, the members of the group lost even that money.
So the only difference between the two groups was that for one, the triumph was highlighted and for the other the failure.
However, by checking the hypothesis of neurologists, the members of the group who played "against failure" were willing to bet even more than the members of the control group and the "winer" group.
"These results cannot be deduced from any previous economic theory.
For those so far explained the phenomena of auctions only with the joy of winning and the prevention of risks.
Only the visual neurological methods helped to resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so that we now come to a third explanation" - Andrew Schotter, professor of the college of economics at the University of New York, established.
Hepatitis: When should you go to your doctor?
Around the world, some 500 million people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and in Hungary, chronic liver disease is considered one of the main causes of death.
The number of infected in this country is estimated at one hundred thousand, but only seven thousand receive treatment because many of the sick do not know they are infected.
The name of hepatitis is the common name of different liver diseases caused by viruses.
Symptoms are very similar; liver and jaundice infections are characteristic, but their pathogens and disease are very different.
Hepatitis viruses depending on the pathogen are propagated by two main forms: hepatitis A and E by food (e.g. with water or contaminated food), hepatitis B, C, D and other blood viruses and body humors (sperm, vagina mood, saliva).
It is recommended that travellers are protected by vaccine against A and B virus, and no vaccines are available from C.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two or three weeks after consuming the infected food, manifests through a general condition, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After that they appear in the skin and in the white of the eyes jaundice, the excrement becomes clear, the dark urine and healing can last even two - three weeks.
Every year one million people die in cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that, according to the calculations, only one in ten infected receives pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: without treatment it can produce liver cirrhosis and even cancer.
Most of the infected do not know that they are ill because this pathological agent slowly destroys liver cells and often the first symptoms only appear 20-30 years later.
Premature recognition, systematic medical control, is therefore very important.
This disease is much more frequent in three groups: people who had blood transfusions before 1991, drug users and tattooers.
There are currently about 200 million people worldwide suffering from chronic hepatitis C.
As this disease can be discovered with routine laboratory control as well, it is worth consulting with the family doctor when experiencing some unknown symptoms.
The disease is cured if it is discovered in time, it is possible to eradicate the virus from the body, so it can suppress the infection and prevent cancer.
On 30 September, the World Hepatitis Day was organized for the first time in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
Its aim is to draw attention to the causes of chronic liver infections caused by viruses and the importance of their premature recognition.
Does it hurt less who believe in God?
According to a recent investigation, religious faith has a soothing effect that also alleviated the death of the martyrs of Catholicism.
Scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment: they analyzed that religious belief in how it influences human pain - the British newspaper Telegraph reported.
In the framework of this unique experiment they applied electric shock to 12 Catholic believers and to the same amount of atheists, while all were looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the scanning technique of the human brain, it was possible to verify that Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for the regulation of pain.
This experiment is the first of the series of research in which, alongside academics, scientists, philosophers and theologians from the different departments of the University participate.
The analysis occurred in the following way; they fixed a chipping instrument to the left hand of the patient, which applied the electric shock.
The researchers asked the participants of the experiment to set their gaze in two paintings; to the Virgin Mary, work of Sassoferrato of the 17th century and to the Lady of the Armiño of Leonardo da Vinci of the 15th century.
The researchers hoped that the spectacle of the Virgin Mary would provoke a certain religious spirit among the faithful, while they chose Leonardo's oil because it was not too different from the other, and they thought it had a reassuring effect.
Patients spent half an hour in a MRI scanner, receiving in that period 20 electric shocks in four successive parts while observing the painting of religious theme or the other.
The Catholics said that by looking at the Virgin Mary they felt in "security" as people "protected", "the peace was calmed down and in their hearts peace reigned".
Observing the religious theme picture, they felt 12 percent less pain than when they looked at Leonardo's work.
Psychologist Miguel Farias, who also participated in the experiment, thinks that with any image so striking you can get a similar effect with atheists as well, you just have to find the right image.
"We should find the portrait of a person for whom they feel very positively, as for a mother or a father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican bishop Tom Wright celebrated the result of the investigation.
"The exercise of faith should and in many cases really change our personality" - Wright added.
After these formidable results there is only one question: what would be the effect on the regulation of pain if shown to the faithful the Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of her size?
Would the vision of a high-quality Virgin Mary bring even better results?
